================================================================================
Origin and acknowledgement
================================================================================

andes began as an effort to improve MS-GF+ and evolved into an independent
algorithm and tool — with its own peptide-spectrum scoring, its statistical
models trained on our own data, and its own implementation. We gratefully
acknowledge MS-GF+ as the origin and inspiration for this work.

Users citing andes should also cite the foundational MS-GF+ publication:

  Kim, S. and Pevzner, P.A. (2014). "MS-GF+ makes progress towards a universal
  database search tool for proteomics." Nature Communications 5:5277.

See HERITAGE.md for the lineage of this project.
